Year = {2023},
Volume = {45},
Number = {7},
Pages = {8110-8126},
Month = {JUL 1},
Abstract = {Bootstrap aggregating (Bagging) and boosting are two popular ensemble
   learning approaches, which combine multiple base learners to generate a
   composite model for more accurate and more reliable performance. They
   have been widely used in biology, engineering, healthcare, etc. This
   article proposes BoostForest, which is an ensemble learning approach
   using BoostTree as base learners and can be used for both classification
   and regression. BoostTree constructs a tree model by gradient boosting.
   It increases the randomness (diversity) by drawing the cut-points
   randomly at node splitting. BoostForest further increases the randomness
   by bootstrapping the training data in constructing different BoostTrees.
   BoostForest generally outperformed four classical ensemble learning
   approaches (Random Forest, Extra-Trees, XGBoost and LightGBM) on 35
   classification and regression datasets. Remarkably, BoostForest tunes
   its parameters by simply sampling them randomly from a parameter pool,
   which can be easily specified, and its ensemble learning framework can
   also be used to combine many other base learners.},
